{
  "texts": [
    "(a) The input AMR graph is processed to remove re-entrancies, yielding a tree structure.",
    "(b) This tree is then used by a tree-to-text transducer, which (c) generates the final text output.",
    "Fig. 7.7Fig.7.",
    "Parsing and AMR-to-text Generation Tasks for Non-English Languages.",
    "Approaches shown are: (A) direct AMR parsing using target-language annotation guidelines; (B) cross-lingual AMR parsing to generate English AMRs from non-English sentences, and AMR-to-text generation to produce sentences in the target language from English AMRs."
  ]
